      "side": 1,
      "message": "The html_insert_assets rule below appends a timestamp to any referenced files. For instance, this is what my bazel-bin/machine/pages/development/index.html file looks like:\n\n  \u003c!DOCTYPE html\u003e\u003chtml\u003e\u003chead\u003e\n      \u003ctitle\u003eMachine State\u003c/title\u003e\n      \u003cmeta charset\u003d\"utf-8\"\u003e\n      \u003cmeta http-equiv\u003d\"X-UA-Compatible\" content\u003d\"IE\u003dedge\"\u003e\n      \u003cmeta name\u003d\"viewport\" content\u003d\"width\u003ddevice-width, initial-scale\u003d1.0\"\u003e\n    \u003clink nonce\u003d\"{% .Nonce %}\" rel\u003d\"stylesheet\" href\u003d\"/static/index.css?v\u003d27396986\"\u003e\u003c/head\u003e\n    \u003cbody class\u003d\"body-sk\"\u003e\n      \u003cmachine-server-sk\u003e\u003c/machine-server-sk\u003e\n\n\n  \u003cscript nonce\u003d\"{% .Nonce %}\" src\u003d\"/static/index.js?v\u003d27396986\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\u003c/body\u003e\u003c/html\u003e\n\nI think this should achieve the same cache busting effect. WDYT?",
